{
  "_comment": "CloudTrail events for an AWS MCP Server OAuth session (agent traffic), modeled on the AWS Security Blog 'Introducing OAuth support for AWS MCP Server' (09 JUL 2026).",
  "_notes": [
    "An agent connects to the AWS MCP Server. AuthorizeOAuth2Access records the browser authorization; CreateOAuth2Token mints the OAuth access token.",
    "The distinguishing marker for MCP agent traffic is requestParameters.resource pointing at the AWS MCP Server (aws-mcp.<region>.api.aws/mcp or aws-mcp.amazonaws.com).",
    "CreateOAuth2Token carries additionalEventData.signInSessionArn (and grant_type). This signInSessionArn is the correlation key.",
    "Per the release, every subsequent AWS API call made with the OAuth access token carries the same aws:SignInSessionArn context (sessionContext.signInSessionArn). trailtool tags those sessions as SessionType 'agent'.",
    "This is distinct from aws login (see aws_login_session.json), which correlates by roleID + creationDate and produces SessionType 'login'."
  ],
